        conseils: "To optimise your transfer from the 2nd arrondissement to CDG, here are our recommendations. Book in advance, especially if your flight departs between 6am and 10am, a very popular time slot. The Sentier quarter and Rue Montorgueil can be congested with morning deliveries before 9am; give the driver a pickup address that is accessible by car. Hotels on Boulevard Montmartre or Rue de la Paix generally have a drop-off space in front of their entrance. For residences on Rue Réaumur or Rue d'Aboukir, the driver can briefly double-park while loading luggage. Allow 3 hours before a long-haul flight and 2.5 hours for European flights. Check your terminal before departure: CDG has three main terminals and inter-terminal shuttles take 15-20 minutes. If travelling with bulky luggage, our sedan offers a spacious boot, and a van can be booked for groups of 5 to 7.",
