      en: {
        metaTitle: "Taxi Paris 4e → Aéroport CDG | 30 km, from €53 | TaxiNeo",
        metaDescription: "A1 route, approximately 45 min. Le Marais, Place des Vosges and Porte de Bagnolet along the way. Terminal drop-off, real-time flight tracking included.",
        heroTitle: "Taxi Paris 4th Arrondissement → CDG Airport",
        heroSubtitle: "Transfer from the Marais and Île de la Cité to Charles de Gaulle at a fixed price of €53 — €65. Door-to-door pickup at your address.",
        description: "The 4th arrondissement, a jewel of Paris with the Marais, Notre-Dame, Place des Vosges and Île Saint-Louis, offers access to CDG via the north-eastern routes. Your TaxiNeo driver picks you up at your address and takes you to your terminal in about 45 minutes.",
        routeDescription: "From the 4th arrondissement, the driver heads up Rue de Rivoli or Boulevard Henri IV towards Bastille, then joins Boulevard Voltaire and Porte de Bagnolet to take the A3 towards CDG. Alternatively, via Porte de la Chapelle and the A1.",
        introduction: "The 4th arrondissement of Paris is one of the most iconic and most visited districts in the French capital. It encompasses most of the Marais, a historic quarter whose 17th-century mansions now house museums, art galleries and designer boutiques. Place des Vosges, the oldest royal square in Paris completed in 1612 under Henri IV, forms an exceptional architectural setting with its red brick pavilions and arcades. The Île de la Cité, the birthplace of Paris with Notre-Dame Cathedral undergoing restoration after the 2019 fire, and the Île Saint-Louis, a peaceful residential haven with refined addresses, form the geographical heart of the city. The Centre Pompidou, a contemporary architectural masterpiece by Renzo Piano and Richard Rogers, attracts millions of visitors each year. The Hôtel de Ville, seat of Paris City Hall, dominates its namesake square with its neo-Renaissance facade. Travellers staying in the 4th arrondissement — international tourists, couples on romantic getaways, business professionals — frequently need a transfer to Charles de Gaulle airport. TaxiNeo provides daily pickups from hotels on Rue Saint-Antoine, Rue de Rivoli, Quai de l'Hôtel de Ville and Île Saint-Louis.",
        itineraire: "The journey from the 4th arrondissement to CDG follows a route optimised by our experienced drivers. Departure is usually via Rue de Rivoli or Rue Saint-Antoine, two main arteries of the district. The driver then heads up to Place de la Bastille via Boulevard Henri IV, then takes Boulevard Voltaire or Boulevard Richard-Lenoir towards the north-east. The ring road is reached at Porte de Bagnolet, from where the A3 motorway heads north to join the A1 at the Garonor interchange. This A3-A1 connection is often smoother than direct access via Porte de la Chapelle, as it avoids crossing northern Paris. If the A3 is congested, the driver may opt for Porte de la Villette or Porte de Pantin. Real-time GPS allows selection of the best route based on traffic conditions. Allow 45 minutes under normal conditions and up to 65 minutes during peak hours between 7-9:30am or 5-7:30pm. The journey passes through Saint-Denis, alongside the Stade de France then the Villepinte Exhibition Centre before reaching the terminals.",
        conseils: "For a stress-free transfer from the 4th arrondissement to CDG, here are our recommendations. The Marais has narrow medieval streets that are often pedestrianised; give the driver the exact pickup address and specify whether your street is accessible by car. For hotels on Rue de Rivoli or Rue Saint-Antoine, pickup is easy on these wide arteries. However, for addresses on Rue des Rosiers, Rue des Francs-Bourgeois or Rue Vieille-du-Temple, the driver may need to position on an adjacent accessible street. The Île Saint-Louis has narrow streets but easy access via Quai d'Anjou or Quai de Béthune. Allow 3 hours before a long-haul flight and 2.5 hours for European flights. On Sundays, the Marais is particularly lively with open shops and strollers; allow 10 extra minutes to leave the district. For early morning departures before 6am, streets are clear and the journey takes only 35 minutes. Check your CDG terminal (T1, T2A-G or T3) before departure.",
        comparaisonTransport: "From the 4th arrondissement, the RER B is accessible from Châtelet-Les Halles station, a 10-minute walk (€12.10 per person, 45-50 min). The Roissybus from Opéra requires a prior 15-minute metro ride (€16.60, 60-75 min). Bus 350 from Gare de l'Est is a 20-minute metro ride away (€6.10, 70-90 min). Public transport is impractical with suitcases in the crowded RER corridors. A ride-hailing service costs between €50 and €95 depending on time and demand, with no price guarantee. TaxiNeo offers a fixed flat rate of €53 to €65 for 4 passengers, about €13 per person in a group. Door-to-door comfort from your Marais hotel and no connections make the taxi the ideal solution.",
        faq: [
          { question: "Where does the driver pick me up in the 4th arrondissement?", answer: "The driver comes to your exact address: outside your hotel in the Marais, on Quai de l'Hôtel de Ville, Rue Saint-Antoine, or on Île Saint-Louis. For pedestrian streets, they position on the nearest accessible street and contact you by SMS." },
          { question: "What is the price of a taxi from the 4th arrondissement to CDG?", answer: "The flat rate is €53 to €65 for a sedan (up to 4 passengers) and €78 for a van (up to 7 passengers). This price is guaranteed with no surcharge for traffic jams." },
          { question: "How long does the journey take from the Marais?", answer: "Allow about 45 minutes under normal conditions and up to 65 minutes during peak hours. On weekends, the Marais streets are lively but the routes to CDG remain smooth." },
          { question: "Can the driver pick me up on Île Saint-Louis?", answer: "Yes, our drivers access Île Saint-Louis via Quai d'Anjou or Quai de Béthune. Provide your precise address and the driver will find the best stopping point nearby." },
          { question: "Is there a surcharge for oversized luggage?", answer: "No, the flat rate includes standard luggage. Our sedans accommodate 2-3 large suitcases. For a group with more luggage, book a spacious van at €78." }
        ],
      },
