        comparaisonTransport: "From the 7th arrondissement, the journey to Orly by public transport goes via the RER C from Invalides or Pont de l'Alma station to Bibliothèque François-Mitterrand, then the extended line 14 to Orly (about €12, 45 min total). The Orlybus from Denfert-Rochereau requires a prior metro line 13 ride from Varenne or Saint-François-Xavier (€11.50 + metro, 50 min). Tram T7 is too far to be practical. A ride-hailing service costs between €35 and €70 depending on time and demand, with no fare guarantee. TaxiNeo offers a flat rate of €36 to €45 for 4 passengers, or €9 per person. No public transport offers the comfort of a pickup at the foot of the Eiffel Tower with direct delivery to the terminal.",
